---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import CTABlock from '../../components/CTABlock.astro';
import { business, BASE } from '../../data/business';
import { postBySlug, postsBySlugs, RELATED_POSTS } from '../../data/posts';
import RelatedPosts from '../../components/RelatedPosts.astro';
import BlogHero from '../../components/BlogHero.astro';
import BlogFigure from '../../components/BlogFigure.astro';

const post = postBySlug('kitchen-tap-replacement-ayrshire')!;
const relatedPosts = postsBySlugs(RELATED_POSTS[post.slug] ?? []).slice(0, 3);
const siteUrl = business.siteUrl.replace(/\/$/, '');
const url = `${siteUrl}/blog/${post.slug}/`;
const ogImage = `${siteUrl}${BASE}/gallery/ayrshire-kitchen-refit-belfast-sink-granite-15-1600w.jpg`;

const articleSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Article',
  '@id': `${url}#article`,
  headline: post.title,
  description: post.description,
  inLanguage: 'en-GB',
  datePublished: post.date,
  dateModified: post.date,
  author: {
    '@type': 'Person',
    name: post.author,
    worksFor: { '@id': `${siteUrl}/#business` },
  },
  publisher: { '@id': `${siteUrl}/#business` },
  image: [ogImage],
  mainEntityOfPage: url,
  articleSection: 'Plumbing',
  keywords: [post.keyword, 'kitchen tap fitter ayrshire', 'monobloc mixer tap kilmarnock', 'tap swap cost ayr', 'leaking kitchen tap KA5'],
  wordCount: post.wordCount,
  about: { '@type': 'Place', name: 'Ayrshire, Scotland' },
};
---
<BaseLayout
  title={`${post.title} | Sorn Handyman Services`}
  description={post.description}
  canonicalPath={`/blog/${post.slug}/`}
  ogImage={ogImage}
  extraSchema={articleSchema}
>
  <Breadcrumbs trail={[
    { name: 'Home', href: `${BASE}/` },
    { name: 'Blog', href: `${BASE}/blog/` },
    { name: post.title },
  ]} />

  <article class="container-x py-10 lg:py-14 max-w-3xl">
    <header>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-amber-600">
        <span>{post.area}</span>
        <span aria-hidden class="text-navy-900/20">·</span>
        <span class="text-navy-900/60">{post.readMinutes} min read</span>
        <span aria-hidden class="text-navy-900/20">·</span>
        <time datetime={post.date} class="text-navy-900/60">{post.dateDisplay}</time>
      </div>
      <h1 class="mt-4 font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-navy-900 leading-tight">
        {post.title}
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-5 text-lg text-navy-900/75">
        A straight kitchen tap swap in Ayrshire usually takes about an hour on
        site. Here is what pushes the price up, what a cheap B&Q tap gets you
        in three years, and the isolator-valve check we do before anything
        else. Every tap job is priced individually — phone or WhatsApp for a
        free no-obligation quote.
      </p>
    </header>
    <BlogHero slug="ayrshire-kitchen-refit-belfast-sink-granite-15" />


    <div class="prose-sorn mt-8 text-lg cv-auto">
      <p>
        A dripping kitchen tap is the job folk put off the longest and ring us
        about the most. Left alone, a slow drip wastes roughly 5,500 litres a
        year, stains a ceramic sink, and — if the flexi hose underneath lets
        go — floods a kitchen in about three minutes. The fix is usually a
        straight-swap. This is the honest version of what a
        <a href={`${BASE}/services/plumbing/`}>kitchen tap replacement</a>
        actually costs, how long it takes, and the two checks that stop the
        cheap job turning into a wet one.
      </p>

      <h2>How we quote in Ayrshire</h2>
      <p>
        We provide a free no-obligation quote for every job, and we price each
        tap swap individually. The price depends on the tap you want, the
        condition of the isolator valves, whether it's a straight swap or a
        two-hole-to-single conversion, and whether new flexis or isolators are
        needed. WhatsApp a photo of your tap and the under-sink cupboard to
        <a href={`${BASE}/areas/kilmarnock/`}>Kilmarnock</a>,
        <a href={`${BASE}/areas/ayr/`}>Ayr</a>, Troon or anywhere else in the
        KA postcodes — phone 07900 255876 or WhatsApp 07472 223323.
      </p>

            <div class="not-prose my-8">
        <BlogFigure slug="ayrshire-bath-reseal-04" />
      </div>

      <h2>How long a straight swap actually takes</h2>
      <p>
        On site, a clean straight-swap with working isolators is about 45
        minutes. Allow an hour with a chat and a test. A rough breakdown:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Shut off isolators under the sink, confirm dead — 3 minutes.</li>
        <li>Disconnect old flexis, remove backnut, lift old tap out — 10 minutes.</li>
        <li>Clean the sink deck, fit new seal, drop new tap in, tighten backnut — 15 minutes.</li>
        <li>Connect new flexis, check for cross-thread, re-pressure — 10 minutes.</li>
        <li>Turn water back on, bleed air out of cartridge, test hot and cold — 5 minutes.</li>
        <li>Silicone bead round the base where the deck is not flat — 5 minutes.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Where it doubles in time: if your isolator valves are seized, if the
        backnut is rusted solid under a stainless sink, or if the old tap was
        a two-hole layout that needs the spare hole blanking. None of those
        are deal-breakers, they just add half an hour and one or two extra
        parts.
      </p>

      <h2>The isolator-valve check — before anything else</h2>
      <p>
        The first thing we do under the sink is turn both isolator valves off
        and check they actually stop the water. Half the older
        <a href={`${BASE}/areas/mauchline/`}>Mauchline</a> and
        <a href={`${BASE}/areas/cumnock/`}>Cumnock</a> kitchens have
        isolators that have not been touched in fifteen years — the slotted
        stem turns, but the gate inside has corroded open. If we did not
        check, we would undo the flexi and get a face full of mains water.
      </p>
      <p>
        If the isolators are seized, we replace them while we are in there —
        a small job, about ten minutes per side. Worth doing. The next
        time you need a tap, a dishwasher or a new flexi, you will not be
        ringing the stopcock the minute the job starts.
      </p>

      <h2>Cheap tap vs mid-range — what you actually get</h2>
      <p>
        A budget Screwfix own-brand mixer will work fine on day one. The
        plastic cartridge inside is rated for around three years of domestic
        use. After that, the handle gets stiff, the spray aerator blocks with
        Ayrshire’s hard water, and the base pivot starts to weep. It is not
        a disaster — a cartridge swap is a small job — but you will likely be
        back at it by year four.
      </p>
      <p>
        A mid-range mixer (Bristan, Grohe Start, Hansgrohe Focus) gets you a
        brass body, a ceramic-disc cartridge rated for 500,000 cycles, and a
        spray aerator that unscrews for a vinegar soak. Most of them carry a
        5-year guarantee. For a kitchen you actually use, that is the better
        spend.
      </p>

      <h2>FAQ</h2>

      <h3>Can I buy my own tap or do you supply?</h3>
      <p>
        Either works. Supply your own and we fit it for the labour rate.
        We can also source a mid-range mixer for a small mark-up on trade
        price and deliver it with us on the day. Your call.
      </p>

      <h3>Do I need to turn the mains off?</h3>
      <p>
        Only if the isolator valves are missing or seized. Ninety per cent
        of the time we work off the under-sink isolators and the rest of
        your house has water the whole job through.
      </p>

      <h3>What about hard-water build-up?</h3>
      <p>
        Ayrshire water is moderately hard. On a mid-range tap, run a
        white-vinegar soak through the aerator twice a year and it will
        outlast the ten-year mark. Cheap aerators are riveted on and have
        to be replaced when they block.
      </p>

      <h3>Do you cover out-of-hours?</h3>
      <p>
        Yes. We run 24/7 call-out across the KA postcodes for burst pipes,
        split flexis and leaking taps — see the
        <a href={`${BASE}/blog/24-7-emergency-handyman-ayr/`}>24/7 emergency
        page</a> for what the out-of-hours minimum covers. Small plumbing
        jobs also sit inside our wider
        <a href={`${BASE}/services/property-maintenance/`}>property
        maintenance</a> round for landlords and Airbnb hosts.
      </p>

      <h3>Where exactly do you cover?</h3>
      <p>
        All of KA1 Kilmarnock, KA5 Sorn and Mauchline, KA7 Ayr, KA12 Irvine
        and the rest of the KA postcodes. See
        <a href={`${BASE}/areas/`}>the full coverage map</a>.
      </p>

      <p>
        If the drip under your kitchen tap is getting louder, book it this
        week. A small job now saves a much bigger floor bill later.
      </p>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 rounded-2xl border border-navy-900/10 bg-navy-50/50 p-6">
        <p class="text-sm text-navy-900/60">Written by</p>
        <p class="mt-1 font-serif text-xl font-bold text-navy-900">{post.author}</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-navy-900/75 text-sm">{post.authorBio}</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>

  <RelatedPosts posts={relatedPosts} eyebrow="Keep reading" heading="Related posts" variant="tinted" />

  <CTABlock
    heading="Dripping tap? We'll swap it this week."
    sub="WhatsApp Fraser a photo of the tap and the under-sink cupboard — firm price back inside the hour across Ayrshire."
    location="Ayrshire"
  />
</BaseLayout>
